    "job_link" : "https://www.quora.com/Can-I-avail-tax-benefits-on-an-education-loan?-",
    "answer" : "Hi! Yes, there is a tax benefit on education loan. The interest payable on the education loan is exempted from tax in India. This tax deduction can only be availed by Individuals and not HUF(Hindu Undivided Family), company or partnerships under section 80E. However, to avail the tax benefit you must take the loan from either from a government recognized financial institution or charitable institutes. Loans taken from relatives or friends are not eligible for tax deductions. Also, the education loan taken you for any of the following are allowed for tax exemption: SpouseChildrenStudent for whom you are the legal guardianTenure: From the year of first installment paid, the deduction can be claimed by the individual for a maximum of 8 years. There is no condition on the place for pursuing higher  Continue Reading Educational loans are not deductible. The interest you pay on the loan may be deductible, but there are strict limits: You can deduct up to $2,500 of student loan interest paid in a given year. As with many tax rules, there is an income limit to this deduction. Your modified adjusted gross income cannot be more than $80,000 (or $160,000 for married couples filing jointly) See Publication 970 (2016), Tax Benefits for Education Now, are the tuition, books and supplies deductible? Yes, there are several benefits for education. The tuition and fees deduction allows you to take up to $4,000 off your taxable income per year. You can deduct tuition, fees, and expenses required to be paid to qualified educational institutions as a condition of enrollment. You do not have to itemize your deductions t Continue Reading Yes you can avail the benefits on education loan provided loans are taken for higher education. Amount paid by individual by way of interest taken from any bank/nbfc or any financial institution shall be allowed as deduction. Deduction is available for 8 years, beginning from the year in which you have paid the interest on loan.",
    "date" : ISODate("2021-02-25T06:03:57.777Z"),
    "question" : "Can I avail tax benefits on an education loan? ",
    "source" : "Quora"
}

