    "job_link" : "https://www.quora.com/Does-Amity-University-give-an-education-loan?-",
    "answer" : "Hello! I am not so aware about Amity University, But I can help you with choosing a right university. Before finalising any institute check the following: 1. Accreditations and Rankings 2. Faculty exposure 3. International Tie-ups 4. Placement One of my friend's daughter was keen to take admission in BBA. After inquiring alot from many institutions, we finally planned to take admission in LPU because of the following: 1.Rankings: LPUs Business School is ACBSP accredited, its a US based organization which provides accreditation services to business school all around the world, so you are getting a degree accredited by USA. Just updating, few days ago, LPU's B-School has been ranked among top 50 institutes by NIRF 2020. LPU has more than 30000 students from more than 70 countries studying in various 250 courses including business programs which shows a direct correlation with the quality or standard which LPU ensures to provide to satisfy the standards at various levels. 2. LPU offers following types of BBA: 1. BBA 2. BBA (Hons.) 3. BBA (International Finance) 4. BBA (Financial Markets) 5. BBA (IT) 6. BBA (Rural Management) 7. Integrated BBA-MBA 3. Quality of education is an important parameter which also distinguished this institute from many B-Schools and has good track record of placement of students in companies like The Royal Bank of Scotland, Trident and many more and they are over the moon and many more. 4. Pathways are also floated which actually assist the student to achieve their dream i.e. Corporate Jobs, Government Jobs and Higher Studies. 5. Pedagogy: Focus on case based teaching to develop skills in analytical thinking and reflective judgement by reading and discussing complex, real-life scenarios. Apart from this, emphasis is laid on teaching by use of experiential activities, seminars, business games, role plays, etc and workshops courses are also prioritised. 6. More exposure to the students is given by allotting application-oriented assignments and examination system. 7. The University also floats study abroad programs try giving an opportunity to complete your degree in US, CANADA, AUSTRALIA etc. You can go for student exchange programs on scholarships paying nominal fees, You do foreign internships and process for foreign study from the university itself. The opportunities are endless. I feel lucky that my niece is studying in such an institute of repute and I suggest all aspiring candidates to be the part of it. Hope this helps. All the Best! Through personal experience i can say Yes, it's worth to take an education loan if you have the confidence of paying it back by getting a nice placement after you complete your B.Tech.  The education loan is kept at the highest interest rate by banks but they also wait for you to complete your 4 years of education and wait for 6 months or in some cases upto 1 year to start repayment of the loan. If you have confidence on your studies and your talents that you'll find a job and a good one for that matter then may be you can pay it back easily in 2 years(Considering you get a good package ;) ) Also in india Upto 4 lacs loan doesn't even need a collateral and from a good engineering institute even some private ones you can do it within that amount.  And why is worth? It'll provide you a sense of how to manage your own money and teach you the responsibility of not putting a burden on your parents' shoulders. This video provides complete information on the SBI Global Ed-vantage Education Loan option for study abroad, the application process, and the added benefits and services you will avail while applying through GyanDhan. The video elaborates on the RoI (Rate of Interest) offered in this scheme, benefits in the interest charged through RiNn Raksha Insurance, Processing fee, Processing time & Moratorium period, Margin, etc.  In recent years, NBFCs and Private banks have emerged to provide education loan without collateral. Private banks such as Axis and ICICI offer unsecured abroad education loans upto 40 Lakhs. Incred education loan and Avanse education loan for abroad are offered by the NBFCs with no limit and cover a wide range of courses and colleges. This video explains about education loans with a strong emphasis on unsecured education loans/ Education loan without collateral. Well, choosing a bank for you education loan might be confusing sometimes. There are many factors that we need to keep in mind, every student is different and so are their profile and targeted colleges. In order to get a loan from a Nationalised bank, one needs to provide collateral which is a security against the loan that you get. Security could be Property whose value must be (more than the loan amount required), FD’s (Must be of the same value of loan required at least). In Banks, you need to mortgage the property papers and you can't take them back until you repay the loan amount. Generally you can repay the loan amount till 15 years or 10 years depending upon the policy of the bank. Everyone doesn't have a suitable property or security to provide for the Education Loan, then in that case private lenders are there such as Incred, Avanse, Auxilo, M power which provides loan on the basis of certain factors like college, country, course, Financial Co borrower’s income and credit history. Gyandhan helps you to get the best possible deal from all these options as their education loan counsellors are full of knowledge and they are aware of all the different conditions of various banks. They have tie ups with multiple nationalised banks like SBI, Bank of Baroda, Axis Bank, and NBFCs such as Avanse, Incred, Auxilo as well as International Lenders such as MPOWER. Their education loan counsellors examines the student’s profile and requirements, then let you know all the options and possibilities of getting the loan",
    "date" : ISODate("2021-02-25T06:11:07.216Z"),
    "question" : "Does Amity University give an education loan? ",
    "source" : "Quora"
}

