ssing. The amount varies across different institutions and also differs by the education loan (loan for studies in India vs abroad vs loans for non-degree courses). In general, banks charge no fees or the processing fees is refundable in most cases. SBI charges a nominal fee of Rs.10k for study abroad loans. NBFCs charge a processing fee which varies from 1%-2% of the total loan amount. The final fee is negotiated in most cases and can be as low as 0.5% (though rarely 0) for the NBFCs. Note: Property appraisal costs are incurred by the customer in addition to the processing fees in most cases. For example, BoB charges 7500 for property evaluation. SBI on the other hand will provide a list of agencies that will do the assessment for you in exchange for a fees. The good thing with banks is that in most of the cases, it is a transparent process. They also give you some amount for living expenses. I got to know about GyanDhan through the Internet. I would suggest each and everyone looking for a loan for higher studies to contact them once before taking any step further. I have personally utilised their service. They are very helpful and genuine people. They have tied up with some banks and get you in contact with their representatives in case you require an education loan. Not only that but also they follow up with you and the bank regularly to make sure everything is alright. They also negotiate with their partner banks to give you the best interest rates in case you have something for lesser interest rate. The best part, all this is done free of cost. Their aim to help people get loans so that the person can pursue his or her dream without much headache or running around. It is started by two IITians. This is not any publicity stunt and it's all at no charges. I would personally thank Mr. Saday who was a very wonderful guide to me throughout the process. In case anyone wants to know more you can A2A me. I will give you their contact details and you can then take a call. You can click on the link below and see once. Home | GyanDhan",
