    "answer" : "It's implied in this question that it's related to Home loan and the netted property insurance. It's not mandatory to buy it from SBI. However, it's mandatory to buy it at the time of disbursal of the loan. It can be bought from any IRDAI approved agency and it must include the name of bank too in the policy document. Since the entire process is linked, and since the insurance can easily be processed at the financing bank itself, it's prudent for the customer to take it from the same bank. It's in the interest of both, the customer and the bank that the asset being created from the loan must be insured. Also, the insurance covers only the building part and it's value. Not the land. To quote the bank on its product offering: “The house/flat purchased/constructed with Bank’s finance should be i Continue Reading Legally I don't think there is any such fee liable . When I had gone through the website it was mentioned that no processing fee is involved for granting education loans. But the ground reality was totally different while applying for a loan I was asked to pay 5500/- bugs as processing fee I have no idea why it was so. Either the information on website was wrong or may be my eye sight was poor or may be it was demanded because the officials thought public knows nothing and they will pay anything to get their work done. And that was a sad thing. No it's not, it is completely your choice, no one can pressurized you for that, But it is always in your favour to take a loan protector policy(Rin Raksha) to relief your nominee (if you are not around) from loan liability.",
