    "answer" : "Hi Prudhvi ! Thanks for the A2A !! Study Loans or Education Loans are one of easiest and fastest to access in India. They are generally sought after by those people who wish to pursue higher education but lack the financial muscle to obtain it. As of now, Education Loans are available only for professional courses like engineering, medical, architecture, MBA, MCA etc. So if you wish to pursue a BA or BCom then Banks would be unwilling to lend. Banks are comfortable to lend for those courses which have a bright future. Technical courses pursued abroad also qualify for an education loan. There are two types of financial institutions who cater to such loans. PSU Banks and Private Banks. PSU Banks are not supposed to ask for any security for loans upto 4 lacs but can insist on a third party guara Continue Reading SBI STUDENT LOAN SCHEME A term loan granted to Indian Nationals for pursuing higher education in India or abroad where admission has been secured. Repayment period of upto 15 years after Course Period + 12 months of repayment holiday*No processing / upfront charges will be levied on Education loans.Eligibility A term loan granted to Indian Nationals for pursuing higher education in India or abroad where admission has been secured. Courses Covered a. Studies in India: Graduation, Post-graduation including regular technical and professional Degree/Diploma courses conducted by colleges/universities approved by UGC/ AICTE/IMC/Govt. etcRegular Degree/ Diploma Courses conducted by autonomous institutions like IIT, IIM etcTeacher training/ Nursing courses approved by Central government or the State GovContinue Reading The process of obtaining financial support through the different credit schemes available in India for financing higher education varies based on which type of loan you take. Just so you know, you can approach a bank or NBFC offering education loan - a loan wherein the purpose is defined and the money borrowed can only be used for financing higher education and the related hostel expenses. In addition, people can also go for personal loan available for financing higher education. It would make no difference at all! The tax benefits will remain the same irrespective of which loan you take.The primary co-applicant will be the parents of loan taker.The repayment can be done by either the parent or the student, it doesn’t matter who pays it as long as the EMI is eventually paid off.However, in  Continue Reading",
