    "answer" : "Commercial banks are business organisations and they are not charitable institutions. In fact educational loan is one among the loans classified as priority sector loans and commercial banks should lend at least 40 percent of their loans to priority sector category loans during each financial year Educational loans carry interest rate like any other loans The borrowers who avail educational loans should pay the interest then and there and they should start payment of instalments immediately after six months from the date of getting the job or one year after completion of their studies in case of non employment During certain situations the central government offer interest subsidy for educational loans It means government is willing to undertake payment of interest for educational loans. Howeve Continue Reading The interest rate for education loans are different for different banks. It depends upon various factors like RBI policy rates, cost of funds etc. Initially the loans were linked to bank specific reference rate i.e MCLR which was different for all banks. Recently RBI has advised banks to link retail loans to Repo rate which is communicated by RBI and is same for all banks, However bank may add different risk premium to offer final rate on retail loan including education loan. Hence the rates are different for different banks. Hope it solves your query. Here you are. Help yourself : Education Loan Scheme - Interest Rates  This image of Athirapally Falls, Chalakudy, Thrissur, Kerala is available in Google Images. You may see more about it here : Dinesh Binjola (दिनेश बिन्जोला)'s answer to Have you ever been to the beautiful Athirapally Waterfalls on River Chalakudi in Kerala?",
