ad about SBI’s Global Ed-Vantage Scheme here There are many other banks such as Bank of Baroda or Axis Bank. They also have many student-friendly loan schemes. I’m linking them below for your reference - BOB Education Loan | Bank of Baroda Education Loan Interest Rate Axis Bank Education Loan | Eligibility, Interest Rate and Process If you are still confused about your prospects, you can also check your loan eligibility here. I hope this answer was of help to you. Definitely yes! It has become increasingly easy for students to get an education loan in India. Many lenders also offer the option to apply for the loan online. If you are applying for an education loan for abroad studies then do apply for the loan via GyanDhan. You can complete the entire loan process online from the comfort of your home. Check your loan eligibility to initiate the hassle-free loan process. There are many lenders in the market that offer education loans for studying in India as well as abroad. There are two types of education loans that are offered - Secured Education LoanUnsecured Education LoanWatch this video to know about them -  Some of the features of the education loans offered by Indian lenders - → Loan amount - the maximum loan amount can be INR 1.5 crores on taking the loan from nationalized banks. The loan amount also depends on the type of loan you have taken - a bigger loan amount is sanctioned in the case of secured education loans whereas loan up to INR 40 lakhs is approved in the case of unsecured education loans. → Loan tenure - the maximum duration of the loan can be 15 years. → Repayment - the moratorium period is usually the study period plus 6 months. → Processing fees - lenders charge a minimal fee to process the loan. → Expenses covered - tuition fees, living expenses in the case of education loan for abroad studies. It will also include library and examination fees. Read this blog for more help - Education Loan for Foreign Studies: A Complete Guide for Students If you have any further doubts or queries, do post them on GyanDhan’s Discussion Forum. You will get a response within hours. To know more about your education loan options, get in touch with GyanDhan. We are an education-focused financing platform and help students select the lender that will best suit their needs. We have also partnered with several lenders in the market and offer doorstep document pickup services so that the entire loan process can be completed from the comfort of your home. Best of all? Our services are absolutely free of cost! I hope this helps you. All the best!",
