{
    "_id" : ObjectId("603746b90c817f0398fb9068"),
    "job_link" : "https://www.quora.com/How-much-salary-is-required-to-repay-an-educational-loan-of-25L?-",
    "answer" : "First, let's have a look at the average, minimum, and maximum salaries offered across campuses in the previous Academic Year (Figures for this year would be higher since placements have improved this season)Salary packages offered in Top B-schools like IIMs, XLRI, etc. Assuming that you get the college which offered the minimum amongst the lowest packages in your graduating year (IIM K with 6 lacs in this example- the college can change from year to year, and so can the package). Assuming, further, that you stay at Delhi/Mumbai and have monthly expenses of around ~20-22k (Obviously, if you have got the lowest package, you would have to try and bring down that figure as low as possible). I personally have an average package(11lpa), and I keep my expenses below 20,000 per month. 6 lacs would amount to, typically: 40,000 in-hand per month. So, even if you consider the option that you won't save much in the first 1-2 years, you can still start off with an EMI amount of about 20,000 pm to begin with.This translates to a period of about 10 years.  However, always keep in mind that your educational achievements will stay with you and opportunities will be there if you work hard. I know of quite a few people who started with 6.5-7 lacs in their first year but graduated to 10-10.5 lpa jobs within their second year. Once your income increase, the EMI shouldn't be much of a bother. I would suggest, for CTCs upto 14 lacs, you should keep the loan reimbursement period constant at 6-7 years (you get tax benefits). More than that amount, you can look at decreasing the loan tenure without significantly hampering your lifestyle or your savings. P.S: This is the absolute worst case scenario, considering you get the lowest package possible, you stay in a high-cost-of-living city, etc. I used the EMI calculator on the Enrizon website (www.enrizon.com) to do this quick calculation for you. I am making the following assumptions: Your course is a two year course and 50% of the loan amount is disbursed at the start of both the years.You are making interest repayments during your education and your loan repayments (EMIs) start immediately after you graduateYou take 10 years after your graduate to repay the loan in full.Your Interest Payment in Year 1: 15,00,000 * 15% = Rs. 2,25,000 Your Interest Payment in Year 2: 30,00,000 * 15% = Rs. 4,50,000 Your EMI for 10 Years after Graduation: Rs. 48,400 per month So, your total repayment at 15% interest will be Rs. 2,25,000 + Rs. 4,50,000 + Rs. 48,400*120 = Rs. 64,83,000 If your interest rate was 11% instead, your total repayment would have been Rs. 54,54,000 thereby saving you more than Rs. 10 Lacs. To understand more about Education Loans, please refer to Frequently Asked Questions | Enrizon - Education Finance Marketplace To check your Education Loan Eligibility in less than 30 seconds, please visit Check Your Education Loan Eligibility | Enrizon - Education Finance Marketplace It differs from place to place and University to University. Also the cost of living of your city in Germany determines how much time does it take to repay ! So, I will just narrate you my experience of studying MS in a small town called Bremerhaven. For me, it took 220 euros per semester for 5 semesters from 2010 to 2012. Apart from that, it costed me 200 euros per month for the student hostel and up to 200 to 300 euros additionally for health insurance, food and other expenditures. I roughly spent not more than 13000 euros in a period of 24 + 6 = 30 months. Most of the money I got back while studying in those 30 months itself, as I was doing a student job. I am bad at accounting the money earned and spent, but all I remember is that I earned more than what I spent. I returned some of the money back home while studying and used my own earnings as a student to book flights for vacations. Cheers if you found an MS in Germany. You are going to make money ! You will have excess in your hand, So do not worry about taking a loan !",
    "date" : ISODate("2021-02-25T06:42:01.624Z"),
    "question" : "How much salary is required to repay an educational loan of 25L? ",
    "source" : "Quora"
}

